The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 NIIT results shine

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Oct. 20: NIIT Technologies Ltds net profit rose 78 per cent in the second quarter ended September 2006 to Rs 26.9 crore from Rs 15.1 crore clocked a year ago.

 During the quarter, revenues jumped 49 per cent to Rs 219.9 crore from Rs 147.5 crore in the year-ago period. 

 The operating profit was up 59 per cent to Rs 41.5 crore.

 Of the overall revenues of Rs 219.9 crore, 50 per cent was contributed by Europe, 33 per cent by the US and 17 per cent by Asia-Pacific, including India.

 The IT solutions business contributed Rs 206 crore, while the BPO segment contributed the remaining Rs 13.9 crore.

 Revenues have grown consistently and, now significantly, demonstrating the robustness of our business strategy, said Arvind Thakur, CEO of NIIT Technologies Limited. 




